This folder contains an integrated structural bioinformatics workflow covering raw experimental data evaluation, computational structure refinement, and multi-metric validation benchmarks. The pipeline is used to assess the stereochemical, spatial, and environmental quality of 3D macromolecular models before and after structural optimization.

📁 **Folder Structure**
**raw_data/**
Storage of unrefined, baseline structural data directly downloaded from public macromolecular archives (RCSB PDB).
**refinement_output/**
Execution workspace for structure optimization protocols, loop modeling, and side-chain relaxation outputs (GalaxyRefine).
**validation_reports/**
Structured analytical results generated from independent evaluation suites measuring geometric and interaction quality parameters.

🔄 **Workflow**

Baseline Assessment ➔ Loop & Side-Chain Optimization ➔ Post-Refinement Re-Validation ➔ Benchmark Comparison

-Download target macromolecular structures (.pdb) and establish a control baseline
-Submit unrefined coordinate files to optimization servers to fix steric clashes and side-chain rotamers
-Run optimized 3D outputs through stereochemical and spatial quality verification matrices
-Compile comparative data summaries to track direct metric improvements across the workflow

## 🛠️ Tools Used
-GalaxyRefine Server
-PROCHECK (Ramachandran Plot)
-ERRAT (Non-Bonded Atom Interactions)
-Verify3D (3D-1D Profile Compatibility)
-PDB coordinate format

## 🎯 Objective

This workflow helps in:
-Identifying structural flaws, stereochemical outliers, and bad backbone geometry in protein models.
-Improving the overall thermodynamic stability and side-chain packing configurations of targets.
-Verifying that 3D spatial coordinate models match the structural profiles expected from their amino acid sequences.
-Providing verified, high-quality atomic models optimized for downstream molecular docking and dynamics simulations.
